     <div xml:lang="lat" type="poem">
   <pb facs="3"/>
   <head>Virgilius de litera Pythagorea.</head>
   <l>LItera Pythagorae discrimine secta bicorni</l>
   <l>Humanae vitae speciem praeferre videtur.<note place="margin">
         <gap reason="illegible" resp="#tech" extent="1 span">
            <desc>〈…〉</desc>
         </gap>
      </note>
   </l>
   <l>Nam via virtutis dextrum petit ardua callem,</l>
   <l>Difficilem{que} aditum primū spectantibus offert,</l>
   <l>Sed requiem praebet fessis in vertice summo:</l>
   <l>Molle ostendat iter via lata, sed vltima meta</l>
   <l>Praecipitat captos, voluit{que} per ardua saxa:</l>
   <l>Quisquis enim duros casus virtutis amore</l>
   <l>Vicerit, ille sibi laudem{que} decus{que} parabit:</l>
   <l>At quidedsiam, luxum{que} sequetur inertem,</l>
   <l>Dum fugit oppositos incauta mente labores,</l>
   <l>Turpis inops{que} simul miserabile transiget aevum.</l>
</div>
